DESCRIPTION:Application service mesh frameworks provide many capabilities 
 across all application services in the mesh.  Service level capabilities l
 ike traffic management\, tracing/observability\, policy\, and security imp
 lemented by a common framework are valuable tools for application develope
 rs and administrators.  The Istio community provides tooling for creating 
 service meshes made up of services implemented in containers and/or VMs/ba
 remetal.  This talk will go through an example Istio on Openstack deployme
 nt with services in containers and VM/baremetal instances.  Tim and Arvind
  will describe Openstack features specifically leveraged by the Istio serv
 ice mesh\, including walking through sample Openstack and Istio deployment
  configuration.  Various Istio features will be discussed with the focus o
 n tie in with Openstack capabilities.\n 
